Responsibility

Use of SSSL in operational, infrastructure, AI, governance, industrial, financial, or safety-critical contexts is undertaken entirely at the user’s own responsibility.

SSSL provides:

• structural regime assignment
• finite alphabet discipline
• spectral boundedness verification
• replay-verifiable artifact reproducibility

It does not provide operational authority, regulatory certification, or safety guarantees.


